# VPC Networking Fundamentals

- create an auto mode VPC network with firewall rules and two VM instances .

-  explore the connectivity for the VM instances.

Objectives
-----------
In this lab, you learn how to perform the following tasks:

Explore the default VPC network

Create an auto mode network with firewall rules

Create VM instances using Compute Engine

Explore the connectivity for VM instances


Explore the default network
------------------------------

Each GCP project has a default network with subnets, routes, and firewall rules

The default network has a subnet in each GCP region.

View the subnets
-----------------
1- go https://console.cloud.google.com/networking/networks/

Name	Region	Subnets	Mode	IP addresses ranges	Gateways	Firewall Rules	Global dynamic routing	Flow logs

Notice the default network with its subnets.

View the routes
----------------
Routes : تخبر  VM  and VPC how to send traffic from an instance to a destination
either inside the network or outside of GCP


